A quarter of Australian women live alone in Sydney's affluent Eastern suburbs . 
  70 percent of the women are more likely to have a university degree than the men . 
  The affluent suburbs of Potts Point, Rushcutters Bay and Elizabeth Bay make up nearly 60 percent of solo households . 
  A new study shows that the majority of solo-dwellers have university degrees . 
  The women who live alone are often stigmatised as sad, lonely and socially isolated . 
